$ Excel: View -> Window -> Hide | Unhide

*Hide* hides the current → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Window.

sa:

  View -> Window -> Hide or Unhide is needed, for example, to show or hide  the «global macro template workbook» → Windows/dirs/Users/username/AppData/Roaming/Microsoft/Excel/XLSTART/Personal_xlsb[`Personal.xlsb`].
